  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6956.52 sitting just above the massive +19.4B gamma wall at 6950, dealers are positioned to sell rallies aggressively into this level, creating strong resistance. The PIN regime with 136.5B total GEX suggests dealers will provide liquidity against momentum moves - selling any push toward 7000 (+12.8B wall) and buying dips toward the 6900 support level (+6.9B wall). Key inflection point remains the 6848 flip strike; a break below would shift dealers from stabilizers to momentum accelerators.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to grind sideways between 6900-7000 with strong resistance at current levels.",
